All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CodeAdapter
    a bridge between the UI my codes component that helps fill data into a selected code on my codes page
    CodeInterpreter
    CodeIntepreter is an object that is created from scanning a QR Code while instantiating the following attributes base, score, name1 (first name), name2 (surname), full_name, newCode
    CodeInterpreterActivity
    CodeInterpreterActivity is an activity that displays a QR code image and the interpreted data from the scanned code.
    CodeInterpreterActivityTests
    This class contains test cases for CodeInterpreterActivity class
    CodeInterpreterTests
    This class contains a test method to verify that the QRCode object is generated correctly by the CodeInterpreter class.
    CodeSorting
    Sorts the codes in my codes based on ascending or descending order
    CodeSortingTests
    A class that tests the ascendingCodeSort() and descendingCodeSort() methods in the CodeSorting class.
    ExampleInstrumentedTest
    Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
    ExampleUnitTest
    Example local unit test, which will execute on the development machine (host).
    geolocation
    This object represents a page within the app that occurs after the user takes a photo when posting a QR code and prompts user to add their geo location and add a comment to their post
    GeolocationTests
    This class contains JUnit test cases for the Geolocation class.
    MyCodesPage
    Functionality behind interacting, sorting and viewing the data on the My Codes page
    PhotoPage
    Functionality behind if the user wants to retake a photo after they have taken one when capturing QR code
    PhotoPageTest
    The PhotoPageTest class contains tests that verify the functionality of the PhotoPage activity in the QRMon application.
    QRCode
    Creates a QRCode object that associates the QR code scanned with the following attributes: name, visual, picture, comment, geolocation, hash, url and score
    QRCodeTest
    This class contains unit tests for the QRCode class.
    ScanCodePage
    This page opens and has access to device camera and prompts user to scan a QR Code
    ScanCodePageTest
    This class contains test cases for the ScanCodePage class of the QRMon Android application.
    ScannedCodePage
    Once the user scans the QRCode, it will show the user which creature they got due to each QR code having unique attributes This page allows the user to add a picture or click next while adding comment and/or geolocation
    ScannedCodePageTest
    This class contains test cases for the ScannedCodePage activity in the QRMon application.
    SHAEncryptor
    Transforms data using a hash function - receives string and creates a hash
    SHAEncryptorTests
    A class that tests the SHAEncryptor class for proper encryption of input.
